description: From Latin imprimātur (“let it be printed”), third person singular present subjunctive passive form of imprimere (“to imprint”).

entries.meaning: (printing) An official license to publish or print something, especially when censorship applies.
examples: The Cheats · A Comedy · Written in the Year, M.DC.LXII. Imprimatur, Roger L'estrange. Nov. 5. 1663. By John Wilson

entries.meaning: (by extension) Any mark of official approval.
